{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% block title %} <title> BookBinder </title>{% endblock %}
{% block stylesheet %}
    {{ parent() }}
    <link href="{{ asset('css/Book.css') }}" rel="stylesheet">
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="container py-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="card rounded-3 mb-sm-4 justify-content-sm-center" style="width: 350px; border-color: #6f42c1">
                    <img id="BookPic" class="rounded-3" src="" alt="BookCover">
                    <div class="card-body text-center">
                        <h1 id="BookTitle" class="card-title"> Title loading </h1>
                        <h3 id="nrOfFollowers"> {{ nrFollowers }} Followers </h3>
                        <p id="BookAuthor"> Name Loading </p>
                        <p id="BookDetails" class="BookDetails">
                            Number of pages : {{ pages }} <br>
                            ISBN: {{ isbn }} <br>
                            Rating : {{ rating}} <br>
                            Library : {{ library }} <br>
                        </p>
                        <div class="btn-group buttons">
                            <input type="submit" value="Vote Book" name="Vote_Book" class="BookBtns">
                            <input type="submit" value="Follow Book" name="Follow_Book" class="BookBtns">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-7 ms-lg-5">
                <div class="container">
                    <h1 class="text-center"> What do they say about this book? </h1>
                    <ul class="book_reviews">
                        <li> I absolutely loved "The Great Godden"! It's a beautifully written coming-of-age story with complex characters and a stunning setting. -Olivia</li>
                        <li> This book was a slow burn, but once it got going, I couldn't put it down. The writing is gorgeous and the story is both heartbreaking and hopeful. -Ethan</li>
                        <li> I was completely captivated by the world of "The Great Godden". The author's attention to detail is impressive, and the characters felt so real to me. -Sophia</li>
                        <li> This is the kind of book that stays with you long after you've finished reading it. I found myself thinking about the characters and their struggles for days afterward. -Isabella</li>
                        <li> "The Great Godden" is a quiet, introspective novel that explores themes of love, loss, and identity. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a thought-provoking read. -Anonymous</li>
                        <li> I loved the subtle tension that runs throughout this book. The author does a fantastic job of building up to a powerful, emotional climax. -Anonymous</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h2 class="text-center"> Give review for the book</h2>
                        {{ form(form) }}
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="{{ asset('javascript/api.js') }}"></script>
    <script>fetch_details('{{ isbn }}');</script>

{% endblock %}